FBIS3-16287 "drsov050_b_94019" FBIS-SOV-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Media Issues Ostankino Seen Acquiring Pro-Chernomyrdin Bias MK1103141094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 11 Mar 94 p 2 MK1103141094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Who Calls the Shots at Ostankino?"] [Text] To all appearances, Aleksandr Yakovlev, current chief of the federal television service, has virtually no role to play there; the shots in the television empire are called by his first deputy, Valentin Lazutkin, who has been orienting himself toward Prime Minister Chernomyrdin. MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS has learned from an informed source that things have gone so far that the list of news items for the 21:00 "Novosti" news program is sent during the day to Government Press Service chief Sergeyev for approval. A report on Yegor Gaydar's recent press conference is a case in point: His quips about Chernomyrdin and "laboratory chiefs" liberally quoted by the mass media have disappeared without a trace, and Yegor Timurovich himself was portrayed as an apologizing retiree.
